  <div class="textFootnotes">
    
      <p class="std"><span class="textMark">a</span>In saying the spirit of man is not created the Prophet without any doubt had in mind the intelligence as explained in the <i>Doctrine and Covenants,</i> Sec. 93:29: &ldquo;Man was also in the beginning with God. Intelligence, or the light of truth, was not created or made, neither indeed can be.&rdquo; From this we gather that the intelligence in man was not created, but the Prophet taught very clearly that man is in very deed the offspring of God, and that the spirits of men were born in the spirit world the children of God. See <i>Doctrine and Covenants</i> 76:24.</p>
    
